xial charge radius $r_A =\n0.74(6)\\,\\mathrm{fm}$, extracted using the $z$-expansion to parameterize the\n$Q^2$ behavior of $G_A(Q^2)$, and $g_P^\\ast = 8.06(44)$ obtained using the pion\npole-dominance ansatz to fit the $Q^2$ behavior of the induced pseudoscalar\nform factor $\\widetilde{G}_P(Q^2)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 May 2019 23:41:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 19 Sep 2019 15:00:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-26"}
