ning these data with $P_{\\rm rot}$ for other clusters, we\nconclude that the assumption that mass and age are separable dependencies is\ninvalid. Furthermore, the cluster data show definitively that stars experience\na temporary epoch of reduced braking efficiency where $P_{\\rm rot}$ stall, and\nthat the duration of this epoch lasts longer for lower-mass stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 May 2019 15:55:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 19 May 2019 13:50:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 25 May 2019 11:57:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-10"}
